 watchers.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aChinesische Sprache. 4aSprachplanung. 4aSprachpolitik. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh  aChina.  aChinese Language.  aLanguage Policy and Planning.1 aBo, Li, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDan, Wei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelong, Li, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDingqian, Gu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErhong, Yang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFei, Li, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFenglan, Guo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuilin, Yu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuomin, Zheng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHe, Liu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHousheng, Liu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJia, Li, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJinzhi, Su, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLei, Wang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLi, Cheng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLin, He, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLinlin, Liang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaopeng, Ma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMengjuan, Zheng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMin, Hou, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNianyi, Xu, eco